{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"7d928c32-090e-429a-8eca-93d408ec344c","content":"\n\nHere are the common options depending on your stack:\n\n**ASP.NET Core (dotnet)**\n```bash\ndotnet new webapi --auth Individual    # Identity + local accounts\ndotnet new webapi --auth SingleOrg     # Microsoft Entra ID (Azure AD)\ndotnet new webapi --auth MultiOrg      # Multi-tenant Azure AD\ndotnet new webapi --auth Windows       # Windows/Negotiate auth\n```\n\n**Node.js / Express** — Use packages like `passport`, `jsonwebtoken`, or `express-oauth2-jwt-bearer` with frameworks like Express or Fastify.\n\n**Python / FastAPI** — Built-in support for OAuth2 via `fastapi.security`, or use libraries like `python-jose` for JWT.\n\n**Authentication approaches:**\n| Approach | Best for |\n|---|---|\n| **JWT Bearer tokens** | Stateless APIs, SPAs, mobile |\n| **OAuth2 / OpenID Connect** | Third-party login (Google, GitHub, etc.) |\n| **API Keys** | Simple service-to-service |\n| **Cookie-based** | Server-rendered apps with APIs |\n| **mTLS / Certificates** | High-security service mesh |\n\nWould you like me to scaffold a specific project? If so, let me know your preferred language/framework and auth type.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"15d9f0ca-e5bd-439d-a8d5-e68e22d775a5","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking a general knowledge question about web API project templates and authentication options. This doesn't require any tool calls - I can answer from my knowledge of common frameworks.\n\nLet me provide a concise answer covering the main options.","outputTokens":370},"id":"9615b4ab-45af-4d8a-929f-579c343e3c53","timestamp":"2026-04-03T00:52:36.654Z","parentId":"e14c5cfe-1582-4ebc-bfad-3d66e3713c5c"}
